Managing expectations

Your talk in <5 words

Programs will snip lo...

  • Programs will sometimes snip long titles to x characters
  • Worse, they'll shrink the font till it all fits in a little box

Don't be too fancy

  • A witty joke in your specialty might go over the committee's heads
  • Newbies to a topic attend talks anyway, need to know which ones

Summarize one of your topics in 5 words or less.

Bad Slides

It's bad to write your slides with complete sentences. Not only does this detract from the words you're saying with your mouth, but it creates a wall of text. When a slide has an unreadable wall of text on it, the audience feels anxious that they might miss an important point buried within the paragraph.

Bad contrast

Tiny fonts
